The paper deals with proof systems and their properties, which is a topic in mathematical logic and theoretical computer science. The use of standard inference rules and the mention of Frege and Resolution suggest a focus on proof theory, which falls under the category of Logic in Computer Science (cs.LO). The mention of polynomial inequalities and linear programming suggests a connection to algorithms and optimization, which could fall under the categories of Computational Complexity (cs.CC) or Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI). The use of directed graphs and cycles suggests a connection to graph theory and algorithms, which could fall under the categories of Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) or Discrete Mathematics (cs.DM).
